// A closure whose result is a NULLABLE struct with a LITUNION field (`() => {f: K0} |
// null`) — bare, and wrapped in the nullable-closure niche (`(… ) | null`, a global or
// local). Two seams had to agree for the `$fnsig` keys to match: (1) `objRetWidenAdopt`
// unwraps a NULLABLE expected result so the lambda's `{f: "80"}` literal adopts the
// K0-field shape through the wrapper; (2) `tyToEmitName`'s TyObj field render preserves
// the litunion ALIAS (`{f:K0}`, the i32-atom layout) instead of softening to
// `{f:string}` — the pin and the annotated value call then resolve the SAME struct
// index for the `>n` result token. Divergence was a cast-failure TRAP at the narrowed
